This paper deals with machine learning algorithms and their application to classification tasks. Specifically, it focuses on the use of generative models such as Hidden Markov Models (HMM) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) artificial neural networks to extract temporal information from dynamic data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), or cryptography and security (cs.CR). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the topic of the paper. Computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) are also possible categories as they often deal with sequential data. Cryptography and security (cs.CR) is less likely as it is not directly related to the topic of the paper.
